--- !u!114 &9217137230174820940
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 6552094979431463186}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshProUGUI
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Sanity:

    Sanity is a secondary resource that isn''t as vital as health
    but it is still importent. As sanity decreases, cards in your hand will randomize
    their costs, and when you reach 0 the randomization gets harsher. In addition,
    if your or anothers sanity is decreased past 0, that will be converted into health
    damage. You get all sanity back at rest sites.Enemies have a chance to breakdown
    when their sanity gets low, skipping their turn.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
